    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Not really. The only way to produce such a list is to reexecute all transactions (i.e. do a full sync). That's more and more unrealistic unless you have an insane hardware to throw at it. As Ethereum grows, this gets harder and harder to the point where I don't think anyone would be willing to do it.\r\n\r\nYou could always write a custom transaction tracer, or perhaps use the `callTracer` that's included in v1.8.0 to gather the infos you need. The proper alternative was always to use contracts and events (which are part of consensus, so they are available of fast sync nodes and light clients too).",
